<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>They are the first ever sibling double act to find love on The Bachelorette Australia.</p>

<p>And on Saturday, sisters Elly and Becky Miles revealed they have both found love on the show. </p>

<p>Becky, 30, told Stellar: 'We're very happy with our fellas.'</p>

<p>Scroll down for video </p>

<p>'We're very happy with our fellas': In this week's issue of Stellar, The Bachelorette sisters Elly and Becky Miles revealed they have both found love on the show. Pictured left is Becky, and right is Elly</p>

<p>Elly, 25, revealed there was no issues of jealous or liking the same guy because of their different taste in men.</p>

<p>'We clicked with who we clicked with, and they were completely different,' the younger Miles sister explained.</p>

<p>The former Bachelor contestant's happily ever this season comes after she found herself being sent home by Matt Agnew last year - despite being a fan favourite.</p>

<p>Both loved up! Elly, 25, revealed there was no issues of jealous or liking the same guy because of their different taste in men. 'We clicked with who we clicked with, and they were completely different,' the younger Miles sister explained</p>

<p>Moved on: The former Bachelor contestant's happily ever this season comes after she found herself being sent home by Matt Agnew (right) last year - despite being a fan favourite. 'I haven't spoken to Matt since that night. We weren't meant to be together' she said</p>

<p>'I haven't spoken to Matt since that night. We weren't meant to be together. I accepted that and that's it,' she said.</p>

<p>The trailer for the new season appeared online for the new season - which is the first-ever to feature two sibling Bachelorettes. </p>

<p>Elly and Becky's journey to each finding their Mr Right is the first time ever siblings have joined forces in the Bachelor and Bachelorette franchise in the world.</p>

<p>So happy! While the double Bachelorette surprised many fans of the show, the sisters could not be happier taking that journey together</p>

<p>Dpuble trouble: In the trailer, Becky tells her sister, 'I want to find love next to you. It will be magical,' as they prepare to meet their Bachelors</p>

<p>While the double Bachelorette surprised many fans of the show, the sisters could not be happier taking that journey together. </p>

